# Copy to backend/.env for local dev. On Vercel or FastAPI Cloud, set the same
# variable names in the host’s environment (dashboard / CLI).
#
# FastAPI Cloud: from repo root, `cd backend`, then `fastapi login` and
# `fastapi deploy` (see https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/deployment/fastapicloud/).
# After deploy, set `BACKEND_URL` on the Next.js host to your *.fastapicloud.dev URL.
#
# Optional: comma-separated origins for direct browser → API calls (not needed when
# the Next app proxies `/api/*` via BACKEND_URL). Example:
# CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS=https://your-app.vercel.app,http://localhost:3000

# Required for /rank and Groq-backed flows (https://console.groq.com/keys)
GROQ_API_KEY=

# Optional (default: llama-3.3-70b-versatile)
# GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# Frontend env (BACKEND_URL, etc.) is documented in the "Frontend (Next.js / Vercel)" section below.

# --- Video interview agent (/interview/*) ---
# SQLite (default) or Postgres (Supabase / Neon / RDS).
#
# Supabase (recommended for deploy):
# 1. Project → Settings → Database → copy "URI" (often starts with postgres://).
# 2. Set DATABASE_URL on your FastAPI host (FastAPI Cloud / Vercel env dashboard).
# 3. The app rewrites postgres:// → postgresql+asyncpg:// and disables asyncpg's
#    statement cache for *.pooler.supabase.com:6543 (transaction pooler).
# 4. On first boot, tables are created if INTERVIEW_AUTO_CREATE_TABLES=1 (default).
#    Passwords with @ # etc. must be URL-encoded in the URI.
#
# Examples (replace PROJECT, REGION, PASSWORD):
#   Transaction pooler (serverless-friendly):
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres.PROJECT:PASSWORD@aws-0-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
#   Direct DB (port 5432, if you avoid the pooler):
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:PASSWORD@db.PROJECT.supabase.co:5432/postgres
#
# Local SQLite (default when DATABASE_URL is unset):
# DATABASE_URL=sqlite+aiosqlite:///./interview.db
# Optional; without it, in-memory cache is used for orchestrator / signaling helpers
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
# Create interview tables on startup (1=yes)
# INTERVIEW_AUTO_CREATE_TABLES=1
# INTERVIEW_MAX_QUESTIONS=5
# Combined score threshold (0–100) for APPROVED vs REJECTED when interview completes
# HIRE_COMBINED_THRESHOLD=62
# If combined is unavailable, minimum interview average to approve
# HIRE_INTERVIEW_FLOOR=45
# Weights for aggregate score (must sum to 1.0 recommended)
# AGGREGATOR_WEIGHT_RESUME=0.4
# AGGREGATOR_WEIGHT_TEST=0.3
# AGGREGATOR_WEIGHT_INTERVIEW=0.3
# Use Groq Whisper for audio upload transcription (requires GROQ_API_KEY)
# INTERVIEW_USE_GROQ_TRANSCRIPTION=0

# --- Frontend (Next.js / Vercel) ---
# next.config rewrites `/api/*` → `${BACKEND_URL}/*`. Set on Vercel (Production + Preview):
#   BACKEND_URL=https://fair-hireing.fastapicloud.dev
# (no trailing slash). Redeploy after changing env — rewrites read BACKEND_URL at build time.
#
# Local: create frontend/.env.local if the API is not on 127.0.0.1:8000:
# BACKEND_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000
# Optional: allow Next dev HMR when opening the site by LAN IP (comma-separated hosts)
# NEXT_ALLOWED_DEV_ORIGINS=10.230.40.125,192.168.1.10
